divs: sighting detailsgreetings, i have four digital camera pictures of unknown ufos, one series of two pictures that appear to show an object travelling a likely trajectory from one point ['image1of2'] a distance away from my the porch of my parent's house (one mile away??) to point (b)['image2of2'], roughly parallel above my house. google maps 'calder ave, north vancouver, bc, canada' and the northernmost location of the capilano park\ southernmost point of capilano lake\ (our water reserve) is where the object appeared to be in the first picture, to the second picture where the object appears to be close to the area around calder ave (it nearly visually disappears over the rooftop of our house ) travelling towards the middle part of lynn canyon park. (the time frame between the two images is around 10-15 seconds) the same day (the properities indicate july 8, 2004 it seems), i took a picture of grouse mountain (directly to the right of our house) showing an mysterious object that appears to be uniformly saucer-shaped... you decide. after many, many fruitless days of snapping pictures of clear skies, i took another picture [image 'abovevancouver'] showing two of the same strange objects apparently directly overhead vancouver city. what astounded me is that i did not see these objects in all four pictures. interestingly enough, the reason why i took these random pictures was because the fact that, beforehand, i read on the internet that many people who captured pictures of ufos did not see them at all, but their cameras! so outside with the digital camera on full res and a mind addled by weed... bam! i just hope these aren't snaps of bugs zipping by my camera... it couldn't be! my doubts kept me from publishing these pictures for 3-5 years (blame the wide timeframe on the pot), but... you decide, and share if you think its legit. the objects are there in the pictures. look carefully, they're either faded or tucked in the corners. i'm sending you the whole image file(s) for the truth...good luck. glen parrish
Summary: unseen cigar object captured on digital camera, unseen with unaided eye
